//“Cersei Lannister’s Ring”
or “Crystal Citrine Ring”//✨available in Size 4.5 DM for inquiries
Just got back from the ruins of Westeros and came back with this gem... Here’s a look at one of my newest projects, directly influenced by the world of George R.R. Martin 🙏 One of my favorites things about the show (aside from Emilia Clarke in all her beauty) is the cultural influence represented in the art styles of each country and the history that it follows...
This ring for example: Worn by Cersei Lannister of House Lannister (one of the richest family dynasty in Westeros), this ring is made purely of Citrine: a Crystal which has been historically associated with and said to manifest Wealth and Abundance; a key staple in the Lannister Family. ⚜️✨
💎💎💎
SWIPE LEFT for detail shots
This ring features a 100% natural formation of some Citrine Crystal, all under a hand-Faceted cut and shaped to be worn as a ring. Citrine is said to promote and manifest abundance and prosperity, as well as relieve fear and anxiety... must be why Cersei is seen primarily with this ring and a glass of Wine in her hand. 😅🍷✨ Be sure to check out the videos above and swipe left for details!
💎💎💎
This ring is now #available in a size 4.5, DM for inquiries or check out my website to make this gem yours (clickable link in bio) Really love making replica pieces like these, let me know what y’all think about this ring or Game of Thrones in the comments below!! 👇👇 Much Love and thanks for the support all, and have a great weekend! 🙏🙌❣️✨

Earlier this year I was inspired by a friend of mine to pick up art as a hobby. Over the past 7 months, I have been slowly filling up the pages of a sketch book with original pieces, and it has felt amazing. I find that art is it's own form of meditation. Once you start working on a piece and really get some momentum going, it almost feels like the piece draws itself while you're just along for the ride. It's very satisfying being able to create something and see a finished product.
Having said that, I figured it was time to start sharing some of these pieces with the world. I'm definitely no Picasso or Michelangelo or whatever, but I have a lot of fun working on these; and on the off chance my posts can provide some form of entertainment, or inspire at least 1 other person out there to pick up thier pencil or paint brush, then I will consider that a massive success.

All my pieces are done completely free hand (which is probably obvious haha), using only pencils, colored pencils and occasionally sharpie. I have not dated any of my pieces up to this point but I will be posting them, for the most part, in the order that I completed them. I hope you all enjoy!

This is the first drawing in my sketch book that was started at the beginning of this year, very early on in my art journy. We all gotta start somewhere 👍
